Sentencas: Here we report a novel SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-delta (SFMO)-430L composite anode for the application in the metal supported solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Such an anode is prepared by coating a thin nano porous and mixed electronic-ionic conducting SFMO layer onto the internal surface of a micron porous 430L alloy backbone.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific polarization resistance of the composite anode for hydrogen oxidation can be as low as 0.11 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electronic conductivity of the 430L alloy support is found to be critically important for promoting rapid hydrogen oxidation kinetics and attaining such a low polarization resistance as the fuel cell anode.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A metal-supported fuel cell with the SFMO impregnated 430L composite anode exhibits outstanding power densities at 800 degrees C, e.g., 0.81 W cm(-2) in hydrogen and 031 W cm(-2) in iso-octane.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Preliminary results show that the present SFMO-430L composite anode exhibits much higher tolerance for coking formation than the traditional Ni-based anode.
Titulo: SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ impregnated 430L alloys for efficient fuel oxidation in metal supported solid oxide fuel cells
